## Router Configuration

The `Router` object defines which model to use for different scenarios:

```json
{
  "Router": {
    "default": "provider,model-name",
    "background": "provider,model-name",
    "think": "provider,model-name",
    "longContext": "provider,model-name",
    "longContextThreshold": 60000,
    "webSearch": "provider,model-name",
    "image": "provider,model-name"
  }
}
```

### Router Types

| Type | Purpose | Example Use Case |
|------|---------|------------------|
| `default` | General coding tasks | Main model for most work |
| `background` | Background operations | File searches, simple tasks (use local/cheap model) |
| `think` | Reasoning-heavy tasks | Plan mode, complex problem solving |
| `longContext` | Long context handling | Large codebases, many files |
| `longContextThreshold` | Token threshold for long context | Default: 60000 tokens |
| `webSearch` | Web search tasks | Requires model with web search support |
| `image` | Image-related tasks | Vision models for screenshots, diagrams |

### Example Router Configuration

```json
{
  "Router": {
    "default": "deepseek,deepseek-chat",
    "background": "ollama,qwen2.5-coder:latest",
    "think": "deepseek,deepseek-reasoner",
    "longContext": "openrouter,google/gemini-2.5-pro-preview",
    "longContextThreshold": 60000,
    "webSearch": "gemini,gemini-2.5-flash",
    "image": "openrouter,anthropic/claude-sonnet-4"
  }
}
```

**Strategy**: Use local/cheap models for background tasks, powerful models for complex reasoning.

