## Best Practices

### Security
- Never commit API keys to git
- Use environment variables for sensitive data
- Set `APIKEY` if exposing router over network
- Keep `HOST` as `127.0.0.1` unless needed

### Cost Optimization
- Use local models (Ollama) for background tasks
- Route simple tasks to cheaper models
- Use powerful models only for complex reasoning
- Monitor API usage through logs

### Performance
- Use `background` routing for file operations
- Set appropriate `API_TIMEOUT_MS`
- Consider local models for faster response
- Use `longContext` routing to avoid token limits

### Configuration Management
- Keep config in version control (without API keys)
- Use environment variables for secrets
- Document your routing strategy
- Test configuration with `ccr ui`

